line_1: Would tire your Lordship's Patience each;
Well met (he cries) and happy sure for each,
line_2: For I am pleas'd to learn, and you to teach;

line_1: Nor, proudly, to be taught unwilling, each
line_2: The Hive is up in arms — expert to teach,

line_1: "Greater or less, more or less perfect each.
Is but to lay proportion'd loads on each;
line_2: And all that freedom's highest aims can reach,
Are nameless Graces which no Methods teach,
And which a Master-Hand alone can reach.
Alternately the nations learn and teach;
